HEADWORD: Spleeny
<hw>Spleen"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Irritable; peevish; fretful.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Spleeny</qex> Lutheran, and not wholesome to⟦br⟧
